Quarterly Insights































Why PPMA






  












Why PPMA
PPMA follows a straightforward, investment-led business model. This means that all aspects of our organization have been built with the primary goal of producing superior performance results for our clients. Our employees, infrastructure and culture all reflect this objective.
Strong Human Capital*

Roughly half of our staff are investment professionals
We have approximately 45 portfolio/asset class managers and 40 analysts
Our investment professionals average 16 years of investment experience and 11 years tenure at our company
Employees have earned over 120 graduate degrees and over 100 professional designations (e.g. CFA, CPA)

Robust Infrastructure

Dedicated portfolio managers, shared research and streamlined decision-making promote scalability of our investment processes, without sacrificing in-depth analysis and idea generation
We have a sophisticated data architecture fueled by a centralized data warehouse that feeds compliance, performance, attribution and reporting tools
Transparency is a main objective in the design of our systems and processes

Productive Culture
We  have clearly defined core operating principles, which guide how we run our  business and interact with our clients and each other. They include the  following:


Focusing  on our clients: Our number one priority is our clients. We stay focused on  understanding their needs and delivering the best solutions to meet those needs.


Delivering results: We align our compensation, processes and  culture with the straightforward goal of consistently delivering superior  investment results to our clients.


Maintaining the highest ethical standards: We operate with integrity and make decisions  consistent with the most ethical course of action – without compromise.


Continually reassessing and improving our  business: To  continually deliver superior results, we change and innovate as our clients' needs change.


Working  collaboratively: We believe we get better results for our clients by  leveraging one another's strengths and treating each other with respect and  sincerity.


Being  team players: By working as teams, we maximize the value derived from  diverse opinions and accumulated knowledge.


Communicating openly: We communicate both considerately and candidly. We think this approach leads to better results – particularly when tough  decisions need to be made.


Having a  sense of community: Our employees fuel our commitment to contributing to the social and economic well-being of the  communities in which we live and work.



*As of 31 December 2016.

















